FBIS4-53959 "dreas100_a_94030" FBIS-EAS-94-100 Daily Report 23 May 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Sumitomo Electric Head Named Kankeiren Chief Sumitomo Electric Head Named Kankeiren Chief OW2305121194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1143 GMT 23 May 94 OW2305121194 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Osaka, May 23 KYODO -- The Kansai Economic Federation (Kankeiren) on Monday [23 May] appointed Tetsuro Kawakami as its chairman to succeed Osamu Uno, who is retiring. The selection of Kawakami, chairman of Sumitomo Electric Industries Ltd., was adopted at a board meeting. The federation is a business lobby representing Kansai-based firms. Uno told a press conference after the meeting that the last days of his seven-year term were focused on pulling the economy out of the recession. Kawakami chose as one of his priority projects during his term a grandiose scheme to build a commercial and residential town near the Kansai International Airport, slated to open in early September, as well as other projects designed to boost the status of Osaka as a key hub of Asia.
